{"body": "Sec.  438.58  Conflict of interest safeguards.\n\n    (a) As a condition for contracting with MCOs, PIHPs, or PAHPs, a \nState must have in effect safeguards against conflict of interest on \nthe part of State and local officers and employees and agents of the \nState who have responsibilities relating to the MCO, PIHP, or PAHP \ncontracts or the enrollment processes specified in Sec.  438.54(b). \nThese safeguards must be at least as effective as the safeguards \nspecified in chapter 21 of the Office of\n\n[[Page 33482]]\n\nFederal Procurement Policy Act (41 U.S.C. 2101-2107).\n    (b) A State may not use an MCO, PIHP, PAHP, or other contractor to \ndetermine beneficiary compliance with the community engagement \nrequirement in part 435, subpart F of this subchapter, unless the \nentity is not, and has no direct or indirect financial relationship \nwith, an MCO, PIHP, or PAHP that is responsible for providing or \narranging for covered services for individuals enrolled with it under \nits contract with the State.", "citation_label": "42 CFR 438.58", "citation_path": "us/regulation/42/438/58", "document_class": "regulation", "expression_date": "2026-07-31", "heading": "Conflict of interest safeguards", "id": "80660948-323b-5d9a-b457-3373f12c366e", "identifiers": {"cfr:part": "438", "cfr:section": "438.58", "cfr:title": "42", "federal-register:citation": "91 FR 33348", "federal-register:document-number": "2026-11094"}, "jurisdiction": "us", "kind": "section", "language": "en", "legal_identifier": "42 CFR 438.58", "level": 2, "metadata": {"chapter": "IV", "part": "438", "section": "438.58", "source_document_citation_path": "us/rulemaking/federal-register/2026-06-03/2026-11094", "source_document_number": "2026-11094", "source_document_title": "Medicaid Program; Community Engagement Requirement for Certain Individuals", "source_document_type": "interim_final_rule_with_comment_period"}, "ordinal": 5800, "parent_citation_path": "us/regulation/42/438", "parent_id": "1fedb9b8-d808-5f1b-8346-d352733b6c3d", "source_as_of": "2026-06-03", "source_document_id": "2026-11094", "source_format": "federal-register-raw-text-slice", "source_id": "federal-register", "source_path": "sources/us/regulation/2026-06-03-cms-2454-ifc-42-cfr-conforming-amendments-r2026-07-15-self-contained/official-documents/release-scope-us-regulation-2026-06-03-cms-2454-ifc-42-cfr-conforming-amendments-r2026-07-15-self-contained", "source_url": "https://www.federalregister.gov/documents/2026/06/03/2026-11094/medicaid-program-community-engagement-requirement-for-certain-individuals", "version": "2026-06-03-cms-2454-ifc-42-cfr-conforming-amendments-r2026-07-15-self-contained"}
{"body": "Sec.  431.213  Exceptions from advance notice.\n\n* * * * *\n    (d) The beneficiary's whereabouts are unknown and the post office \nreturns agency mail directed to him indicating no forwarding address \n(see Sec.  431.231(d) for procedure if the beneficiary's whereabouts \nbecome known). The provisions of this paragraph (d) sunset on October \n1, 2034. CMS will follow applicable rulemaking procedures to ensure \nthat policies governing whereabouts unknown are implemented and \neffective on October 1, 2034, replacing the policies scheduled to \nsunset on that date;\n* * * * *", "citation_label": "42 CFR 431.213", "citation_path": "us/regulation/42/431/213", "document_class": "regulation", "expression_date": "2026-07-31", "heading": "Exceptions from advance notice", "id": "586a2746-e283-5e66-b8fd-ec37eafb26dc", "identifiers": {"cfr:part": "431", "cfr:section": "431.213", "cfr:title": "42", "federal-register:citation": "91 FR 33348", "federal-register:document-number": "2026-11094"}, "jurisdiction": "us", "kind": "section", "language": "en", "legal_identifier": "42 CFR 431.213", "level": 2, "metadata": {"chapter": "IV", "part": "431", "section": "431.213", "source_document_citation_path": "us/rulemaking/federal-register/2026-06-03/2026-11094", "source_document_number": "2026-11094", "source_document_title": "Medicaid Program; Community Engagement Requirement for Certain Individuals", "source_document_type": "interim_final_rule_with_comment_period"}, "ordinal": 21300, "parent_citation_path": "us/regulation/42/431", "parent_id": "feb548cc-f9a0-5548-819e-a40724854745", "source_as_of": "2026-06-03", "source_document_id": "2026-11094", "source_format": "federal-register-raw-text-slice", "source_id": "federal-register", "source_path": "sources/us/regulation/2026-06-03-cms-2454-ifc-42-cfr-conforming-amendments-r2026-07-15-self-contained/official-documents/release-scope-us-regulation-2026-06-03-cms-2454-ifc-42-cfr-conforming-amendments-r2026-07-15-self-contained", "source_url": "https://www.federalregister.gov/documents/2026/06/03/2026-11094/medicaid-program-community-engagement-requirement-for-certain-individuals", "version": "2026-06-03-cms-2454-ifc-42-cfr-conforming-amendments-r2026-07-15-self-contained"}
{"body": "Sec.  431.231  Reinstating services.\n\n* * * * *\n    (d) If a beneficiary's whereabouts are unknown, as indicated by the \nreturn of unforwardable agency mail directed to him, any discontinued \nservices must be reinstated if his whereabouts become known during the \ntime he is eligible for services. The provisions of this paragraph (d) \nsunset on October 1, 2034. CMS will follow applicable rulemaking \nprocedures to ensure that policies governing when a beneficiary's \nwhereabouts become known are implemented and effective on October 1, \n2034, replacing the policies scheduled to sunset on that date.", "citation_label": "42 CFR 431.231", "citation_path": "us/regulation/42/431/231", "document_class": "regulation", "expression_date": "2026-07-31", "heading": "Reinstating services", "id": "5de663eb-808d-5ea4-a664-aec8fbea49d3", "identifiers": {"cfr:part": "431", "cfr:section": "431.231", "cfr:title": "42", "federal-register:citation": "91 FR 33348", "federal-register:document-number": "2026-11094"}, "jurisdiction": "us", "kind": "section", "language": "en", "legal_identifier": "42 CFR 431.231", "level": 2, "metadata": {"chapter": "IV", "part": "431", "section": "431.231", "source_document_citation_path": "us/rulemaking/federal-register/2026-06-03/2026-11094", "source_document_number": "2026-11094", "source_document_title": "Medicaid Program; Community Engagement Requirement for Certain Individuals", "source_document_type": "interim_final_rule_with_comment_period"}, "ordinal": 23100, "parent_citation_path": "us/regulation/42/431", "parent_id": "feb548cc-f9a0-5548-819e-a40724854745", "source_as_of": "2026-06-03", "source_document_id": "2026-11094", "source_format": "federal-register-raw-text-slice", "source_id": "federal-register", "source_path": "sources/us/regulation/2026-06-03-cms-2454-ifc-42-cfr-conforming-amendments-r2026-07-15-self-contained/official-documents/release-scope-us-regulation-2026-06-03-cms-2454-ifc-42-cfr-conforming-amendments-r2026-07-15-self-contained", "source_url": "https://www.federalregister.gov/documents/2026/06/03/2026-11094/medicaid-program-community-engagement-requirement-for-certain-individuals", "version": "2026-06-03-cms-2454-ifc-42-cfr-conforming-amendments-r2026-07-15-self-contained"}
{"body": "Sec.  600.320   Determination of eligibility for and enrollment in a \nstandard health plan.\n\n* * * * *\n    (b) Timely determinations. The terms of Sec.  435.912 of this \nchapter (relating to timely determinations of eligibility under the \nMedicaid program) apply to eligibility determinations for enrollment in \na standard health plan exclusive of Sec.  435.912(c)(3)(i) and (e)(3). \nThe standards established by the State must be included in the BHP \nBlueprint.\n* * * * *", "citation_label": "42 CFR 600.320", "citation_path": "us/regulation/42/600/320", "document_class": "regulation", "expression_date": "2026-07-31", "heading": "Determination of eligibility for and enrollment in a standard health plan", "id": "fab96acc-e9b3-5209-ac0a-baee2a1315bd", "identifiers": {"cfr:part": "600", "cfr:section": "600.320", "cfr:title": "42", "federal-register:citation": "91 FR 33348", "federal-register:document-number": "2026-11094"}, "jurisdiction": "us", "kind": "section", "language": "en", "legal_identifier": "42 CFR 600.320", "level": 2, "metadata": {"chapter": "IV", "part": "600", "section": "600.320", "source_document_citation_path": "us/rulemaking/federal-register/2026-06-03/2026-11094", "source_document_number": "2026-11094", "source_document_title": "Medicaid Program; Community Engagement Requirement for Certain Individuals", "source_document_type": "interim_final_rule_with_comment_period"}, "ordinal": 32000, "parent_citation_path": "us/regulation/42/600", "parent_id": "96c9d911-1059-5b49-aa9e-2442ba33683b", "source_as_of": "2026-06-03", "source_document_id": "2026-11094", "source_format": "federal-register-raw-text-slice", "source_id": "federal-register", "source_path": "sources/us/regulation/2026-06-03-cms-2454-ifc-42-cfr-conforming-amendments-r2026-07-15-self-contained/official-documents/release-scope-us-regulation-2026-06-03-cms-2454-ifc-42-cfr-conforming-amendments-r2026-07-15-self-contained", "source_url": "https://www.federalregister.gov/documents/2026/06/03/2026-11094/medicaid-program-community-engagement-requirement-for-certain-individuals", "version": "2026-06-03-cms-2454-ifc-42-cfr-conforming-amendments-r2026-07-15-self-contained"}
{"body": "Sec.  457.340  Application for and enrollment in CHIP.\n\n* * * * *\n    (d) Timely determination of eligibility. (1) The terms in Sec.  \n435.912 of this chapter, exclusive of Sec.  435.912(e)(3), apply \nequally to CHIP, except that standards for transferring electronic \naccounts to other insurance affordability programs are pursuant to \nSec.  457.350 and the standards for receiving applications from other \ninsurance affordability programs are pursuant to Sec.  457.348. The \nprovisions of this paragraph (d)(1) sunset on October 1, 2034. CMS will \nfollow applicable rulemaking procedures to ensure that policies \ngoverning timely determinations of CHIP eligibility are implemented and \neffective on October 1, 2034, replacing the policies scheduled to \nsunset on that date.\n* * * * *", "citation_label": "42 CFR 457.340", "citation_path": "us/regulation/42/457/340", "document_class": "regulation", "expression_date": "2026-07-31", "heading": "Application for and enrollment in CHIP", "id": "1984d185-6e8c-5956-b812-eca5c429d255", "identifiers": {"cfr:part": "457", "cfr:section": "457.340", "cfr:title": "42", "federal-register:citation": "91 FR 33348", "federal-register:document-number": "2026-11094"}, "jurisdiction": "us", "kind": "section", "language": "en", "legal_identifier": "42 CFR 457.340", "level": 2, "metadata": {"chapter": "IV", "part": "457", "section": "457.340", "source_document_citation_path": "us/rulemaking/federal-register/2026-06-03/2026-11094", "source_document_number": "2026-11094", "source_document_title": "Medicaid Program; Community Engagement Requirement for Certain Individuals", "source_document_type": "interim_final_rule_with_comment_period"}, "ordinal": 34000, "parent_citation_path": "us/regulation/42/457", "parent_id": "19463eaf-54f0-576a-bca8-001f3858a27b", "source_as_of": "2026-06-03", "source_document_id": "2026-11094", "source_format": "federal-register-raw-text-slice", "source_id": "federal-register", "source_path": "sources/us/regulation/2026-06-03-cms-2454-ifc-42-cfr-conforming-amendments-r2026-07-15-self-contained/official-documents/release-scope-us-regulation-2026-06-03-cms-2454-ifc-42-cfr-conforming-amendments-r2026-07-15-self-contained", "source_url": "https://www.federalregister.gov/documents/2026/06/03/2026-11094/medicaid-program-community-engagement-requirement-for-certain-individuals", "version": "2026-06-03-cms-2454-ifc-42-cfr-conforming-amendments-r2026-07-15-self-contained"}
